        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "In playing around with the Lucene_Search tool, I ran into a PHP Fatal error when trying to load large amounts of data (actually, not all that much data, but around 200,000 varchar(100) text fields): PHP FATAL ERROR: Allowed memory size of 104857600 bytes exhausted (tried to allocated 119 bytes) in Zend\/Search\/Lucene\/Analysis\/Analyzer\/Common\/Text.php on line 65. and PHP FATAL ERROR: Allowed memory size of 104857600 bytes exhausted (tried to allocated 64 bytes) in Zend\/Search\/Lucene\/Index\/SegmentWriter.php on line 480. \n\nI am curios if there are any known restrictions on the amount of data you can use when building the Lucene search documents? \n"
        },
